Islote de Perejil / ⵜⴰⴳⵣⵉⵔⵜ ⵏ ⵜⵓⵔⴰ / جزيرة تورة

Claimed by both Morocco and Spain. Neither claim recognized by other party. Since an armed conflict in 2002 between the parties, it remains unpopulated, and both sides agreed not to occupy it. Spain claims the island as part of the municipality of Ceuta.
